===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Paradise Park had a population of 367. The population density was {{convert|1,320.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Paradise Park was 311 (84.7%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 3 (0.8%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 9 (2.5%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.3%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 8 (2.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 35 (9.5%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 29 persons (7.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Paradise Park CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0655604 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 187 households, out of which 51 (27.3%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 86 (46.0%) were married-couple households, 17 (9.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 43 (23.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 41 (21.9%) had a male householder with no partner present. 43 households (23.0%) were one person, and 22 (11.8%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.96.<ref name=DP1/> There were 123 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (65.8% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Paradise Park CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0655604 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 47 people (12.8%) under the age of 18, 31 people (8.4%) aged 18 to 24, 68 people (18.5%) aged 25 to 44, 125 people (34.1%) aged 45 to 64, and 96 people (26.2%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 50.9{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 106.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 384 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,381.3|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 187 (48.7%) were occupied. Of these, 160 (85.6%) were owner-occupied, and 27 (14.4%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

